text:
Emmons Ave., between Shore Boulevard (left) and East 19th Street, showing a group of houses on the Bay which were demolished by the City of New York in 1934 for the widening of Emmons Ave. Also shown is the Bay partially frozen. This is a set of three views at different angles.
April 2, 1924.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Sheepshead Bay, viewed northwest, showing a view from Shore Boulevard, at the pedestrians bridge in Manhattan Beach. All these houses were used as boat Clubs prior to 1934 when they were razed by the City of New York for the widening of Emmons Ave.

The same, a more limited view.
